File-Attributes

File::Attributes lets you assign attributes to files (and read them,
and list them, and delete them).

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install

If the tests fail, don't install the module.  Instead, file a bug report.

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc File::Attributes

You can also look for information at:

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/File-Attributes

    CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=File-Attributes

    AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/File-Attributes

    CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/File-Attributes

